196
00:16:14.110 --> 00:16:16.310
She'll do well in English conditions.

197
00:16:32.430 --> 00:16:34.230
Who is he?
Why is he on the field?


198
00:16:34.590 --> 00:16:36.310
Ma'am, that's Paddy sir.

199
00:16:36.790 --> 00:16:37.950
Padam Singh Sodhi.

200
00:16:38.750 --> 00:16:40.190
He played a Test match
in the 90s.


201
00:16:40.390 --> 00:16:41.750
But what is he doing here?

202
00:16:44.830 --> 00:16:46.990
Please tell him, team selection
is going on. He can't be there.


203
00:16:47.750 --> 00:16:49.430
Hello... you are?

204
00:16:51.030 --> 00:16:51.870
Anina.

205
00:16:53.190 --> 00:16:54.070
And you, sir?

206
00:16:56.590 --> 00:16:57.630
You don't know who I am?

207
00:17:00.110 --> 00:17:00.790
Shame.

208
00:17:02.710 --> 00:17:03.750
I'm thirsty...

209
00:17:08.590 --> 00:17:09.510
The thirst to play.

210
00:17:15.030 --> 00:17:16.670
- Is that working?
- What, sir?


211
00:17:20.590 --> 00:17:21.990
Sir, that's just--

212
00:17:22.590 --> 00:17:24.390
It's a beautiful morning for cricket.

213
00:17:24.510 --> 00:17:25.310
Sir, sir...

214
00:17:26.350 --> 00:17:27.990
One ball. Just one ball.

215
00:17:29.230 --> 00:17:31.870
Sir, selections are going on...

216
00:17:32.310 --> 00:17:34.190
Sure... I didn't think
elections are going on.


217
00:17:34.510 --> 00:17:35.590
Let me bowl one ball.

218
00:17:35.710 --> 00:17:38.190
Seeing this amazing
batswoman play


219
00:17:38.310 --> 00:17:40.070
I felt like bowling, after 20 years.

220
00:17:40.510 --> 00:17:43.470
After all, the greatest motivation
for a bowler is a good batsman.


221
00:17:43.790 --> 00:17:44.830
Just... one ball.

