01:02:29.430 --> 01:02:31.070
Water has stopped.

798
01:02:35.270 --> 01:02:37.270
"Forget the complaints"

799
01:02:37.590 --> 01:02:39.630
"Soar like an eagle"

800
01:02:40.030 --> 01:02:42.030
"Flapping one wing"

801
01:02:42.150 --> 01:02:44.310
"Rise above your destiny"

802
01:03:45.190 --> 01:03:48.670
Booster is the secret of your energy.

803
01:04:52.910 --> 01:04:53.910
Whoa!

804
01:04:54.670 --> 01:04:56.110
What have you done!

805
01:04:56.790 --> 01:04:57.630
Give me your hand.

806
01:04:57.870 --> 01:04:59.510
No no, what if he sees me
lending a hand?


807
01:04:59.710 --> 01:05:00.790
Just give your hand.

808
01:05:02.430 --> 01:05:04.830
- Aah... is that a hand or a hammer!
- See.


809
01:05:08.990 --> 01:05:11.430
All this gardening
has turned you into Muhammad Ali!


810
01:05:11.550 --> 01:05:12.910
Now I feel like a bowler.

811
01:05:13.030 --> 01:05:14.790
It's a beautiful day at the MCG.

812
01:05:14.910 --> 01:05:16.430
Play is all set to begin.

813
01:05:18.830 --> 01:05:21.310
There is an unwanted spectator
on the field.


814
01:05:23.550 --> 01:05:24.990
Anina from the Pavilion End.

815
01:05:30.190 --> 01:05:32.270
Left-arm... over the wicket.

816
01:05:44.870 --> 01:05:45.630
Short and wide.

817
01:05:45.750 --> 01:05:47.990
The batsman smashes the ball
in his sleep...


818
01:05:48.110 --> 01:05:49.550
for 4 runs.

819
01:05:53.550 --> 01:05:56.070
A rubbish half volley... 6 runs.

820
01:05:59.190 --> 01:06:01.870
2 kms away from the leg stump...

821
01:06:08.750 --> 01:06:10.310
A rubbish full toss.

822
01:06:10.710 --> 01:06:13.430
The ball flies out of the stadium...

823
01:06:15.550 --> 01:06:18.310
If muscles were all a bowler needed,

824
01:06:19.030 --> 01:06:22.030
Muhammad Ali would've been
the world's best bowler.


825
01:06:27.030 --> 01:06:28.670
'I'm a bowler.'

826
01:06:29.710 --> 01:06:31.470
Before you utter these three words...

827
01:06:31.590 --> 01:06:35.630
bowl at least three thousand times!

828
01:06:39.670 --> 01:06:40.390
Bowl!

829
01:06:43.350 --> 01:06:44.310
Pitch it here.

830
01:06:48.950 --> 01:06:49.750
Here.

831
01:06:58.110 --> 01:06:59.150
Get up.

832
01:07:15.230 --> 01:07:16.830
Just look at Bishan Singh Bedi.

833
01:07:17.150 --> 01:07:20.350
Even if I practice for 10 years,
I won't be able to bowl like this.


834
01:07:21.390 --> 01:07:23.150
Congratulations, you're pregnant.

835
01:07:24.310 --> 01:07:26.950
You're comparing yourself
with Bishan Singh Bedi.


836
01:07:27.190 --> 01:07:29.910
Means, there's a bowler
growing inside you.


837
01:07:30.390 --> 01:07:32.790
Waiting to be born.

838
01:07:35.150 --> 01:07:35.830
Hi.

839
01:07:35.950 --> 01:07:37.030
Rasika!

840
01:07:39.990 --> 01:07:42.990
I've told you so many times
to get that fence fixed!


841
01:07:43.190 --> 01:07:44.430
Bloody buffaloes!

842
01:07:44.550 --> 01:07:46.030
See the mess they've made.

843
01:07:47.190 --> 01:07:48.390
What a mess!

844
01:07:48.630 --> 01:07:49.750
Shit!

845
01:07:49.990 --> 01:07:51.430
It's about to rain.

846
01:07:51.950 --> 01:07:52.750
Bowl.

847
01:07:52.870 --> 01:07:53.750
- How?
- Bowl.


848
01:07:53.870 --> 01:07:55.590
- I'll clean this in two minutes.
- We don't have two minutes.


849
01:07:55.710 --> 01:07:56.630
Bowl, come on... 
Bowl bowl bowl!

850
01:07:56.750 --> 01:07:58.030
- The ball will land on the dung.
- Shut up!


851
01:07:59.590 --> 01:08:00.870
Left-arm around the wicket.

852
01:08:01.150 --> 01:08:01.990
Hurry up!

853
01:08:08.670 --> 01:08:10.670
A good length delivery...
on the off stump.


854
01:08:10.830 --> 01:08:12.230
The batsman had to defend.

855
01:08:18.630 --> 01:08:19.830
Correct line... on the middle stump.

856
01:08:19.950 --> 01:08:21.750
The batsman defends again.

857
01:08:25.590 --> 01:08:27.110
Full length... a beautiful delivery

858
01:08:27.310 --> 01:08:29.030
No big shot played.

859
01:08:29.150 --> 01:08:31.110
One perfect ball after another.

860
01:08:31.230 --> 01:08:32.670
I had my heart in my mouth.

861
01:08:33.150 --> 01:08:34.470
What if the ball lands on the dung!

862
01:08:35.790 --> 01:08:36.990
He's a genius.

863
01:08:37.190 --> 01:08:39.270
You're the one who bowled,
how is he the genius?


864
01:08:39.430 --> 01:08:40.990
This is short pitched...

865
01:08:43.950 --> 01:08:45.070
This is over pitched...

866
01:08:45.190 --> 01:08:46.390
This is outside the off stump...

867
01:08:46.510 --> 01:08:47.470
And this is outside leg stump.

868
01:08:47.590 --> 01:08:50.310
If the ball lands
here... here... here...


869
01:08:50.430 --> 01:08:51.830
it's a shit ball.

870
01:08:52.350 --> 01:08:55.790
I've been avoiding the dung and
aiming at the gaps while bowling.


871
01:08:55.910 --> 01:08:57.230
The line and length became perfect.

872
01:08:57.350 --> 01:08:58.030
Shit!

873
01:08:58.150 --> 01:09:00.550
Shit is a good fertilizer for growth!

874
01:09:02.110 --> 01:09:05.430
Till you can bowl perfectly
with your eyes closed...


875
01:09:06.070 --> 01:09:06.710
Bowl!

876
01:09:16.630 --> 01:09:20.030
Why is it so important for you
to make her a cricketer?


877
01:09:22.230 --> 01:09:24.950
When something is snatched away
from someone without reason...


878
01:09:25.830 --> 01:09:26.990
it's wrong.

879
01:09:34.670 --> 01:09:39.510
Looks like God has sent you here
to rectify His mistakes.


880
01:09:43.430 --> 01:09:44.670
Give me some more nectar.

881
01:09:44.790 --> 01:09:46.470
- No more.
- What!


882
01:09:46.830 --> 01:09:49.030
From now on, I'll be the one
rectifying mistakes.


883
01:09:49.390 --> 01:09:50.390
It's a Dry Day, from today.

884
01:09:50.550 --> 01:09:52.550
Damn woman!
Who are you to shut my bar?


885
01:09:52.990 --> 01:09:56.870
I am that woman, who would've died a man
if not for you.


886
01:09:58.350 --> 01:09:59.990
You understood my reality,

887
01:10:00.230 --> 01:10:01.910
fought with my family,

888
01:10:02.230 --> 01:10:03.310
helped me get operated,

889
01:10:03.430 --> 01:10:05.310
gave me a new identity,

890
01:10:05.430 --> 01:10:06.590
adopted me as your sister...

891
01:10:06.710 --> 01:10:08.390
Your liver... I will not let it die!

892
01:10:12.110 --> 01:10:13.150
Liver?

893
01:10:14.550 --> 01:10:15.790
If I don't drink one day,

894
01:10:15.910 --> 01:10:18.750
my liver will message
the other workers of my body...


895
01:10:19.230 --> 01:10:22.190
'Boss is dead. 
Stop work now!'

896
01:10:22.310 --> 01:10:23.790
Shutter down.

897
01:10:24.270 --> 01:10:25.630
I'll truly die.

898
01:10:30.350 --> 01:10:32.750
Then who will rectify
your God's mistakes?


899
01:10:43.750 --> 01:10:45.630
I don't understand...

900
01:10:49.550 --> 01:10:52.310
how did the buffaloes shit
in the perfect spots?


901
01:11:30.030 --> 01:11:31.030
Happy Diwali!

902
01:12:07.910 --> 01:12:08.870
Happy Diwali!

903
01:12:09.070 --> 01:12:10.270
Happy Diwali!

904
01:12:14.750 --> 01:12:15.990
Happy Diwali, sir.

905
01:12:20.190 --> 01:12:22.150
Sir... this is Jeet.

906
01:12:22.990 --> 01:12:24.390
Jeet, Paddy sir.

907
01:12:24.670 --> 01:12:26.750
- Hello, sir. Happy Diwali.
- I'm not happy!


908
01:12:29.510 --> 01:12:31.910
You have to be happy today, sir.

909
01:12:32.190 --> 01:12:35.150
You're not allowed to sit alone
in the dark.


910
01:12:40.070 --> 01:12:41.070
Bowl.

911
01:12:45.270 --> 01:12:46.430
How, sir?

912
01:12:49.830 --> 01:12:50.510
Bowl!

913
01:13:35.310 --> 01:13:37.390
Now please be a little happy, sir.

914
01:13:41.710 --> 01:13:42.430
Would you have...

915
01:13:45.670 --> 01:13:47.710
got out to your own bowling?

916
01:13:48.510 --> 01:13:51.150
Once upon a time,
you used to bat, right?


917
01:13:51.390 --> 01:13:53.630
Could you take your own wicket?

918
01:13:54.710 --> 01:13:55.670
Forget that...

919
01:13:55.790 --> 01:13:59.390
could you at least beat your bat
with this bowling?


920
01:14:02.070 --> 01:14:03.070
No?

921
01:14:05.070 --> 01:14:08.150
So then... what do I have
to be so happy for?


922
01:14:11.230 --> 01:14:12.630
More importantly...

923
01:14:14.590 --> 01:14:16.510
what are you so happy for?

924
01:14:18.470 --> 01:14:21.790
Pitching a ball on the right spot
doesn't make anyone a bowler.


925
01:14:22.870 --> 01:14:23.790
Wickets.

926
01:14:24.110 --> 01:14:25.870
A bowler's job is to take wickets.

927
01:14:26.110 --> 01:14:30.270
And you're not capable of taking
even a tail-ender's wicket.


928
01:14:32.190 --> 01:14:35.270
I've been staying up nights thinking...

929
01:14:35.590 --> 01:14:37.830
how will this girl take wickets?

930
01:14:37.990 --> 01:14:39.710
What does a spinner have except

931
01:14:39.830 --> 01:14:41.870
the art of deceiving the batsman

932
01:14:42.150 --> 01:14:43.910
and the magic of playing
with the batsman's mind.


933
01:14:44.070 --> 01:14:45.750
But how will the spinner
weave her magic


934
01:14:45.870 --> 01:14:48.030
if she isn't able to spin the ball?

935
01:14:48.470 --> 01:14:50.830
My head is spinning,
thinking about this.


936
01:14:51.190 --> 01:14:52.150
And you!

937
01:14:52.430 --> 01:14:54.310
You're going around with your lover,

938
01:14:54.550 --> 01:14:57.510
bursting crackers and giving out sweets!

939
01:14:57.950 --> 01:15:00.630
- Sir.
- I'm talking to my player.


940
01:15:05.350 --> 01:15:06.310
Hunger.

941
01:15:06.510 --> 01:15:11.350
The hunger to play for India
is your biggest strength.


942
01:15:11.630 --> 01:15:15.270
If you keep satiating this hunger
with sweet nothings,


943
01:15:15.470 --> 01:15:16.630
you'll be finished!

944
01:15:16.910 --> 01:15:18.790
And you'll have to wait
for Diwali every year


945
01:15:18.910 --> 01:15:19.990
to be happy!

946
01:15:25.710 --> 01:15:26.990
7 a.m. tomorrow.

947
01:15:28.030 --> 01:15:30.070
Stuff cotton in your ears
and go to bed.


948
01:15:30.350 --> 01:15:31.270
Alone!

949
01:15:43.910 --> 01:15:45.150
Leave her hand.

950
01:15:47.310 --> 01:15:48.270
It's fine, it's okay.

951
01:15:49.990 --> 01:15:50.990
Leave her hand.

952
01:15:53.430 --> 01:15:54.590
- I said, leave her hand!
- Sir!


953
01:15:57.510 --> 01:15:58.350
You okay?

954
01:15:59.910 --> 01:16:00.510
Sir...

955
01:16:08.190 --> 01:16:09.190
No!

956
01:16:10.830 --> 01:16:11.950
Let go of her hand
or I'll set you on fire.


957
01:16:12.070 --> 01:16:13.390
- Stop it, sir.
- Leave her hand!


958
01:16:13.510 --> 01:16:14.830
Sir... what are you doing?

959
01:16:17.150 --> 01:16:19.670
It's Diwali... Hold her hand. Boom!

960
01:16:19.790 --> 01:16:20.390
Hold.

961
01:16:20.510 --> 01:16:21.670
- Sir, stop it.
- Dare hold her hand?


962
01:16:21.790 --> 01:16:22.510
Boom!

963
01:16:22.630 --> 01:16:23.950
Diwali! Diwali! Diwali! 
Hold her hand.

964
01:16:24.070 --> 01:16:24.910
Stop it, sir.

965
01:16:25.030 --> 01:16:26.350
Hold, hold. Boom! Boom!

966
01:16:42.390 --> 01:16:45.310
"The lamp burns my soul."

967
01:16:48.870 --> 01:16:50.110
Wickets.

968
01:16:50.910 --> 01:16:52.070
Wickets.

969
01:16:52.630 --> 01:16:53.590
He's a psychopath.

970
01:16:54.790 --> 01:16:56.070
You should've seen him, Granny.

971
01:16:56.190 --> 01:16:58.510
He looked possessed.

972
01:16:59.630 --> 01:17:00.910
Crazy man.

973
01:17:02.030 --> 01:17:03.510
What does he think of himself?

974
01:17:03.790 --> 01:17:05.390
Thinks he's her father?

975
01:17:05.950 --> 01:17:06.950
Bloody fellow!

976
01:17:07.470 --> 01:17:08.590
He came here on his own.

977
01:17:08.750 --> 01:17:11.830
We didn't go begging for his help.

978
01:17:13.150 --> 01:17:14.750
Does he think he owns her?

979
01:17:15.110 --> 01:17:16.310
Torturing her like this!

980
01:17:16.430 --> 01:17:17.430
Exactly.

981
01:17:17.550 --> 01:17:18.630
Exactly.

982
01:17:19.950 --> 01:17:21.030
He does not own her,

983
01:17:21.390 --> 01:17:23.830
he's not her father, brother,
or boyfriend.


984
01:17:24.830 --> 01:17:26.830
He came here uninvited

985
01:17:27.350 --> 01:17:29.990
and took on the responsibility
of her future.


986
01:17:32.870 --> 01:17:35.630
Do you know how much
the monthly electricity bill is?


987
01:17:35.950 --> 01:17:38.110
No one gives electricity, for free.

988
01:17:38.310 --> 01:17:39.470
And this psychopath...

989
01:17:39.590 --> 01:17:42.950
wants to light up the entire life
of a complete stranger, for free!


990
01:17:44.750 --> 01:17:45.950
Crazy man.

991
01:17:55.990 --> 01:17:58.270
I know a coach has to be tough.

992
01:17:58.830 --> 01:18:00.310
But so ruthless.

993
01:18:00.590 --> 01:18:01.750
She's a young girl.

994
01:18:01.870 --> 01:18:03.390
She has lost her arm,
not her heart.


995
01:18:03.510 --> 01:18:05.070
What if something had happened
to the boy?


996
01:18:05.190 --> 01:18:07.830
Why take out your prustration on her?

997
01:18:14.030 --> 01:18:16.270
Yes, I am prustrated.

998
01:18:20.870 --> 01:18:22.870
Pucking prustrated!

999
01:18:24.830 --> 01:18:27.070
My mother died giving birth to me...

1000
01:18:27.430 --> 01:18:29.230
I was born prustrated.

1001
01:18:29.950 --> 01:18:32.110
My father brought home a new wife...

1002
01:18:32.390 --> 01:18:34.350
childhood prustrated.

1003
01:18:35.710 --> 01:18:39.630
Then Cricket took pity on me
and adopted me...


1004
01:18:42.830 --> 01:18:44.990
and my dream came true.

1005
01:18:45.190 --> 01:18:49.190
The dream of playing for India one day.

1006
01:18:50.750 --> 01:18:54.430
One day is all I played for India.

1007
01:18:59.630 --> 01:19:02.430
My entire youth prustrated.

1008
01:19:08.710 --> 01:19:13.230
Logically, I should have got
another chance to play for India


1009
01:19:13.350 --> 01:19:15.030
but this life...

1010
01:19:15.790 --> 01:19:18.150
isn't a game of logic.

1011
01:19:19.310 --> 01:19:20.430
This life...

1012
01:19:21.870 --> 01:19:23.830
is a game of magic.

1013
01:19:24.750 --> 01:19:25.950
Magic.

1014
01:19:28.550 --> 01:19:32.310
But this magic never came
into my life.


1015
01:19:34.310 --> 01:19:36.110
'The system is corrupt.'

1016
01:19:36.550 --> 01:19:38.430
'Politics in the team.'

1017
01:19:38.830 --> 01:19:40.310
'Selectors are puckall.'

1018
01:19:40.430 --> 01:19:45.990
Hearing my constant cribbing,
Magic got prustrated and ran away!


1019
01:19:50.350 --> 01:19:53.310
My hair turned grey.
I stopped talking.


1020
01:19:55.310 --> 01:19:56.750
I stopped living.

1021
01:20:00.510 --> 01:20:04.670
Then, one day suddenly,
there was a knock at my door.


1022
01:20:05.310 --> 01:20:07.590
Opened... saw... it was MAGIC!!!

1023
01:20:08.590 --> 01:20:11.510
'Hello, Paddy. How are you?'

1024
01:20:12.510 --> 01:20:16.550
'Sorry, I couldn't bring magic
to your life.'


1025
01:20:17.990 --> 01:20:21.110
'Try again?
Want another chance?'


1026
01:20:21.430 --> 01:20:23.270
'Here... take Anina. Try.'

1027
01:20:26.070 --> 01:20:29.030
Anina has plenty of talent...

1028
01:20:30.350 --> 01:20:33.630
courage, passion, guts.

1029
01:20:34.110 --> 01:20:35.750
But logically...

1030
01:20:38.030 --> 01:20:40.430
can someone with just one hand
play for the country?


1031
01:20:41.430 --> 01:20:42.190
No.

1032
01:20:43.750 --> 01:20:45.630
You need magic.

1033
01:20:48.510 --> 01:20:51.430
But this damn magic appears

1034
01:20:52.070 --> 01:20:55.430
only when you're 100% ready for it.

1035
01:20:58.830 --> 01:21:01.630
You have to earn the magic!

1036
01:21:02.510 --> 01:21:03.270
Otherwise...

1037
01:21:05.070 --> 01:21:06.910
it's the end of play.

1038
01:21:16.870 --> 01:21:18.550
For a spectator,

1039
01:21:19.470 --> 01:21:21.470
sport is just a game.

1040
01:21:22.710 --> 01:21:24.670
But for players,

1041
01:21:24.790 --> 01:21:29.550
sport is sacrifice.

1042
01:21:33.310 --> 01:21:36.070
What a loser feels...

1043
01:21:37.030 --> 01:21:38.310
I know.

1044
01:21:42.270 --> 01:21:43.990
I know.

1045
01:21:47.390 --> 01:21:49.510
I want her to know...

1046
01:21:50.510 --> 01:21:53.830
how winners feel.

1047
01:22:01.310 --> 01:22:03.510
I also want to know...

1048
01:22:06.310 --> 01:22:08.310
what winners feel.

1049
01:22:19.830 --> 01:22:21.150
Just one day...

1050
01:22:24.830 --> 01:22:27.110
just for one day,
I want to live...


1051
01:22:30.510 --> 01:22:32.070
without prustration.

1052
01:22:36.550 --> 01:22:37.630
For one day.

1053
01:22:43.230 --> 01:22:44.550
Sacrifice.

1054
01:24:50.790 --> 01:24:52.470
Okay now you can spin the ball

1055
01:24:53.150 --> 01:24:54.830
but would you be able
to take your own wicket?


1056
01:24:58.270 --> 01:24:59.030
No.

1057
01:25:00.070 --> 01:25:00.790
Why?

1058
01:25:01.110 --> 01:25:02.950
There's spin but no speed.

1059
01:25:04.030 --> 01:25:05.390
That nip is not there.

1060
01:25:05.630 --> 01:25:08.590
Any half-decent batter
will easily play such slow spin.


1061
01:25:09.150 --> 01:25:10.190
To get a wicket,

1062
01:25:10.310 --> 01:25:12.670
the ball should turn sharply...
like zuckkkk!


1063
01:25:12.990 --> 01:25:14.710
So what the 'zuck' are you waiting for?

1064
01:25:16.350 --> 01:25:18.670
If the ball needs more speed,
bowl with more speed.


1065
01:25:21.030 --> 01:25:21.550
More.

1066
01:25:24.150 --> 01:25:24.870
More!

1067
01:25:25.350 --> 01:25:26.710
Can't bowl faster than this, sir.

1068
01:25:26.870 --> 01:25:27.790
You can.

1069
01:25:29.150 --> 01:25:29.870
Bowl.

1070
01:25:30.790 --> 01:25:31.470
More...

1071
01:25:32.310 --> 01:25:32.990
More.

1072
01:25:38.510 --> 01:25:39.310
We're done.

1073
01:25:40.470 --> 01:25:41.030
Yes.

1074
01:25:47.310 --> 01:25:50.350
If you strain your shoulder,
it may get dislocated again.


1075
01:25:50.630 --> 01:25:52.630
Complete rest for two weeks.

1076
01:25:53.230 --> 01:25:55.110
Why? It's not so serious.

1077
01:25:55.270 --> 01:25:56.950
Now that you've set it,
why can't she bowl?


1078
01:25:57.110 --> 01:25:59.270
I've dislocated my shoulder
multiple times,


1079
01:25:59.510 --> 01:26:01.190
physio used to set it
and I was back on the field.


1080
01:26:01.310 --> 01:26:03.350
Mr Sodhi, get up and bowl.

1081
01:26:04.590 --> 01:26:06.510
Come on, get up... and bowl.

1082
01:26:09.830 --> 01:26:11.070
- Bowl?
- Yeah.


1083
01:26:13.790 --> 01:26:14.670
Stop.

1084
01:26:14.950 --> 01:26:16.750
When you bowl left arm,

1085
01:26:17.070 --> 01:26:20.030
your right arm automatically
swings back.


1086
01:26:20.470 --> 01:26:23.910
The reverse motion of the right arm
creates the momentum


1087
01:26:24.030 --> 01:26:26.670
that gives a left-arm bowler
that extra force.


1088
01:26:27.470 --> 01:26:30.750
That's why your left arm
can generate more pace


1089
01:26:31.190 --> 01:26:32.150
not Anina's.

1090
01:26:32.350 --> 01:26:34.910
To compensate for that momentum,

1091
01:26:35.150 --> 01:26:38.110
if she tries to generate the same force
with only one hand,


1092
01:26:38.230 --> 01:26:40.470
her shoulder could get
permanently damaged.


1093
01:26:41.590 --> 01:26:42.390
So, Anina...

1094
01:26:42.950 --> 01:26:45.550
Yes, sir, I know... basic Physics.

1095
01:26:46.270 --> 01:26:49.430
Mr Sodhi, I'm a doctor
but I'm an Indian too.


1096
01:26:50.070 --> 01:26:52.270
Cricket runs in my blood, too.

1097
01:26:52.950 --> 01:26:55.990
You've done more than you could

1098
01:26:56.590 --> 01:26:57.750
you've done your best.

1099
01:26:58.110 --> 01:26:58.950
Hello.

1100
01:27:00.230 --> 01:27:02.830
You here to offer your sympathies again?

1101
01:27:03.550 --> 01:27:05.350
- I was just trying to--
- Dad, ask him to get out.


1102
01:27:08.630 --> 01:27:11.270
Why is your timing always off?

1103
01:27:12.070 --> 01:27:13.310
Time the ball, no?

1104
01:27:14.630 --> 01:27:18.150
Momentum... how to generate momentum?

1105
01:27:24.550 --> 01:27:26.790
Momentum. Come on think.

1106
01:27:41.790 --> 01:27:42.990
Enough now.

1107
01:27:44.790 --> 01:27:45.710
Get me whisky.

1108
01:27:47.910 --> 01:27:48.910
Spin...

1109
01:27:49.270 --> 01:27:50.190
Momentum.

1110
01:27:51.510 --> 01:27:53.790
This 'mentum mentum'
will make you go mad!


1111
01:27:54.030 --> 01:27:56.270
Not here, idiot! Stupid woman.

1112
01:28:00.110 --> 01:28:01.350
Not on the pitch!

1113
01:28:01.470 --> 01:28:02.990
On the side... at short leg!

1114
01:28:06.910 --> 01:28:08.150
Is this short leg, you fool?

1115
01:28:08.270 --> 01:28:09.510
How do I know where short leg is!

1116
01:28:09.710 --> 01:28:11.230
Do short people field at that position?

1117
01:28:11.710 --> 01:28:13.630
It's not me, it's your cricket
that's foolish.


1118
01:28:13.830 --> 01:28:15.510
It's an English game
but all the English is wrong!


1119
01:28:15.630 --> 01:28:16.270
Short leg...

1120
01:28:16.390 --> 01:28:17.950
And slip?
Does everyone 'slip' over there?


1121
01:28:18.070 --> 01:28:19.310
Shut up and get out!

1122
01:28:19.430 --> 01:28:20.550
I'm already outside!

1123
01:28:20.750 --> 01:28:21.550
Say 'get in'.

1124
01:28:30.070 --> 01:28:32.430
Hey... what just happened?

1125
01:28:32.670 --> 01:28:34.030
'What just happened'?

1126
01:28:34.750 --> 01:28:36.030
I just escaped death.

1127
01:28:46.790 --> 01:28:48.390
We just escaped death.

1128
01:28:50.230 --> 01:28:51.870
Mr Padam Singh? Come in.

1129
01:28:52.830 --> 01:28:53.910
Tea? Coffee?

1130
01:29:01.710 --> 01:29:03.870
Welcome, my 'basic Physics' expert.

1131
01:29:04.550 --> 01:29:06.550
Shall we show the world...

1132
01:29:07.310 --> 01:29:08.430
momentum?

1133
01:29:35.630 --> 01:29:37.830
- Hello, sir.
- Well done, son...


1134
01:29:38.030 --> 01:29:39.470
fantastic absolutely.

1135
01:29:44.510 --> 01:29:46.470
You sent it to 'the' 
Bishan Singh Bedi?

1136
01:29:46.630 --> 01:29:49.830
The greatest left-arm spinner
the world has ever seen.


1137
01:29:50.550 --> 01:29:52.830
Not known for hiding his feelings.

1138
01:29:52.950 --> 01:29:54.950
You guys think Kajal is good, right?

1139
01:29:55.270 --> 01:29:56.350
Kajal can't...

1140
01:29:57.750 --> 01:29:59.510
- Sir, but...
- She hasn't played...


1141
01:30:06.270 --> 01:30:09.670
After the break,
she isn't consistent.


1142
01:30:10.750 --> 01:30:11.990
Bishan Singh Bedi?

1143
01:30:13.310 --> 01:30:14.550
- Carry on, guys.
- Okay.


1144
01:30:14.670 --> 01:30:16.070
- Kajal...
- No no no!


1145
01:30:24.110 --> 01:30:27.510
Guys, you should check this out.

1146
01:30:31.430 --> 01:30:32.510
Unbelievable!

1147
01:30:34.790 --> 01:30:35.790
Is this the same Anina?

1148
01:30:36.030 --> 01:30:37.790
If she doesn't have a twin sister,
it's her!


1149
01:30:38.070 --> 01:30:39.550
How is this possible?

1150
01:30:39.990 --> 01:30:41.190
She wasn't even a bowler.

1151
01:30:41.310 --> 01:30:42.630
There are a lot of free apps.

1152
01:30:42.750 --> 01:30:45.590
You can easily morph your face
on another body.


1153
01:30:50.350 --> 01:30:50.990
Hello?

1154
01:30:51.110 --> 01:30:53.110
Anina, this is Hemanti Dhingra

1155
01:30:53.310 --> 01:30:55.830
from the selection committee, remember?

1156
01:30:56.070 --> 01:30:56.870
Ani...

1157
01:30:57.110 --> 01:30:57.870
'Hello?'

1158
01:30:57.990 --> 01:30:59.030
Yes, ma'am?

1159
01:30:59.230 --> 01:31:00.110
Tell me, ma'am.

1160
01:31:00.230 --> 01:31:01.910
How are you?
Health wealth all okay?


1161
01:31:02.510 --> 01:31:04.270
Wealth same. Health better, ma'am.

1162
01:31:04.790 --> 01:31:06.190
Anina...

1163
01:31:08.830 --> 01:31:11.670
did you see a video?

1164
01:31:12.070 --> 01:31:13.110
Which video, ma'am?

1165
01:31:13.790 --> 01:31:15.430
You didn't see it?
I knew it.


1166
01:31:15.630 --> 01:31:17.350
'Technology is so advanced now...'

1167
01:31:17.590 --> 01:31:20.430
if you see it, you'll truly think
it's you who's bowling.


1168
01:31:20.710 --> 01:31:23.430
Truth will look like the truth, ma'am.

1169
01:31:26.630 --> 01:31:29.430
Are you seriously asking us
to consider her?


1170
01:31:29.710 --> 01:31:30.910
It is our job to make sure,

1171
01:31:31.030 --> 01:31:34.470
there is absolutely no discrimination
of any sort in this game.


1172
01:31:34.750 --> 01:31:37.590
Is she good enough to play
for India or not...


1173
01:31:38.270 --> 01:31:40.230
it is our duty to check that out.

1174
01:31:46.790 --> 01:31:47.710
Thank you, ma'am.

1175
01:31:49.030 --> 01:31:51.070
Granny, they are calling me
for the Indian camp!


1176
01:31:52.510 --> 01:31:55.310
Why are you underacting?
Show some emotion.


1177
01:31:55.910 --> 01:31:57.430
I'm a Federer fan.

1178
01:31:57.590 --> 01:31:59.030
We don't show our emotions.

1179
01:32:42.750 --> 01:32:43.870
Fantastic!

1180
01:32:44.110 --> 01:32:45.910
I've never seen anything like this.

1181
01:32:46.030 --> 01:32:48.150
But, one problem...
she won't be able to bat.


1182
01:32:48.270 --> 01:32:48.910
So?

1183
01:32:49.030 --> 01:32:50.430
B.S. Chandrashekhar couldn't bat.

1184
01:32:50.630 --> 01:32:53.790
Is she good enough to play
as a specialist bowler or not?


1185
01:32:53.910 --> 01:32:55.270
She is amazing.

1186
01:32:55.670 --> 01:32:56.830
A one-handed player...

1187
01:32:56.950 --> 01:32:58.310
in an international cricket team...

1188
01:32:58.550 --> 01:32:59.870
the media will go into a frenzy.

1189
01:33:02.390 --> 01:33:03.990
What a story, ma'am.

1190
01:33:04.790 --> 01:33:08.190
We should renegotiate
the telecast rights.


1191
01:33:08.630 --> 01:33:11.670
Mr Bhavik, I know you're
the Treasurer of the Cricket Board


1192
01:33:12.110 --> 01:33:16.110
but for once, please forget the treasure
and focus on the cricket.


1193
01:33:20.110 --> 01:33:23.350
Welcome to the first
A23 one-day international


1194
01:33:23.470 --> 01:33:25.390
between England and India.

1195
01:33:25.510 --> 01:33:27.750
News from the middle is
that England have won the toss


1196
01:33:27.870 --> 01:33:29.230
and elected to bat.

1197
01:33:35.150 --> 01:33:38.310
It's a historical day
in the game of cricket.


1198
01:33:49.270 --> 01:33:52.110
Look at Anina swinging
her left arm.


1199
01:33:53.030 --> 01:33:56.990
What a way to make
your international debut in cricket.


1200
01:33:57.150 --> 01:33:59.910
What a day for me to make my debut
as a commentator.


1201
01:34:05.070 --> 01:34:07.230
'Start of the innings... first ball.'

1202
01:34:08.230 --> 01:34:09.510
'Archer taking guard.'

1203
01:34:09.750 --> 01:34:12.830
'Six fielders on the offside
and three on the onside.'


1204
01:34:14.870 --> 01:34:17.630
Dipti from the Pavilion End to Archer.

1205
01:34:19.950 --> 01:34:22.190
Archer drives... through extra cover
for 4


1206
01:34:22.310 --> 01:34:23.710
and England are on their way.

1207
01:34:25.710 --> 01:34:26.870
Great wristwork... 4 runs.

1208
01:34:26.990 --> 01:34:28.350
Backfoot punch.
No chance to stop it.


1209
01:34:28.470 --> 01:34:30.110
Over mid-on... 4 runs.
Beautiful cover drive.


1210
01:34:30.230 --> 01:34:33.430
Played to Anina...
Not a clean pick up and throw.


1211
01:34:33.550 --> 01:34:34.710
1 run added.

1212
01:34:36.230 --> 01:34:37.910
Super shot over cover.

1213
01:34:39.350 --> 01:34:40.150
And 6 runs!

1214
01:34:40.270 --> 01:34:42.550
England off to a flying start here.

1215
01:34:43.390 --> 01:34:44.790
The first bowling change...

1216
01:34:44.910 --> 01:34:48.110
it's the girl that
we've all been waiting for.


1217
01:34:48.670 --> 01:34:51.550
The atmosphere is charged with emotion.

1218
01:34:51.670 --> 01:34:52.750
The question is...

1219
01:34:52.870 --> 01:34:55.910
will it play on the minds of the
English batters out in the middle?


1220
01:34:56.030 --> 01:34:59.430
I don't know about the English but
is it okay for an Indian to


1221
01:34:59.830 --> 01:35:01.670
shed a tear or two on live television?

1222
01:35:02.430 --> 01:35:03.630
I'm going to stand up.

1223
01:35:07.750 --> 01:35:08.830
'First match.'

1224
01:35:09.390 --> 01:35:10.510
'First over.'

1225
01:35:10.870 --> 01:35:11.750
'First ball.'

1226
01:35:14.790 --> 01:35:16.790
The entire stadium resounding
with applause.


1227
01:35:21.190 --> 01:35:22.710
Anina from the Pavilion End.

1228
01:35:22.950 --> 01:35:24.750
Left-arm around the wicket.

1229
01:35:26.990 --> 01:35:28.550
A comic moment in this drama.

1230
01:35:28.790 --> 01:35:31.150
Bowler in front of the umpire?
Or umpire in front of the bowler?


1231
01:35:31.270 --> 01:35:33.830
- Ever seen anything like this, Pankaj?
- Never.


1232
01:35:41.670 --> 01:35:43.550
Hearts racing...

1233
01:35:45.030 --> 01:35:49.590
Seems like time itself has stopped.

1234
01:35:56.030 --> 01:35:59.110
A loosener from Anina and
Searle smashes it over midwicket.


1235
01:35:59.230 --> 01:36:02.510
With this 6, Searle's score moves to 48.

1236
01:36:03.070 --> 01:36:04.350
She is in an attacking mood today.

1237
01:36:05.990 --> 01:36:07.350
Anina's second ball...

1238
01:36:10.310 --> 01:36:13.230
Outside the leg stump...
signalled a wide.


1239
01:36:13.830 --> 01:36:16.190
Can't imagine the pressure on the girl.

1240
01:36:16.710 --> 01:36:18.350
The captain is having a chat with her.

1241
01:36:18.550 --> 01:36:21.030
Think she's telling her to focus
on her line and length.


1242
01:36:22.150 --> 01:36:23.310
Anina's next ball...

1243
01:36:27.950 --> 01:36:28.990
This was a good ball.

1244
01:36:29.430 --> 01:36:31.910
Correct line and length.
Searle forced to defend.


1245
01:36:35.590 --> 01:36:37.670
The batter takes two steps
outside the crease.


1246
01:36:37.790 --> 01:36:40.230
Let's see if Anina can adjust
her length.


1247
01:36:43.350 --> 01:36:44.990
Bang on middle stump... correct length.

1248
01:36:45.190 --> 01:36:46.790
No chance to play an attacking shot.

1249
01:36:52.470 --> 01:36:54.510
Slowly gaining confidence...

1250
01:36:55.030 --> 01:36:56.990
Anina is back to her bowling mark.

1251
01:36:59.390 --> 01:37:01.310
In... comes... Anina...

1252
01:37:03.950 --> 01:37:05.070
What was that?

1253
01:37:07.310 --> 01:37:08.550
What was that arrow!

1254
01:37:12.230 --> 01:37:14.190
Batters, spectators...
everyone in shock.


1255
01:37:15.230 --> 01:37:16.470
Just look at that.

1256
01:37:31.710 --> 01:37:33.510
A spinning spinner.

1257
01:37:33.870 --> 01:37:35.350
She is a Ghoomer.

1258
01:37:35.950 --> 01:37:36.990
A Ghoom-what?

1259
01:37:37.230 --> 01:37:38.150
Pacer...

1260
01:37:38.430 --> 01:37:39.390
Spinner...

1261
01:37:40.670 --> 01:37:41.550
Ghoomer!

1262
01:37:46.230 --> 01:37:48.750
'The momentum that's gained
by the swing of the right hand...'


1263
01:37:48.870 --> 01:37:51.430
'will be achieved by spinning
your body.'


1264
01:37:51.630 --> 01:37:53.870
'If you spin, the ball will spin.'

1265
01:37:54.030 --> 01:37:54.670
Zuckkkk!

1266
01:37:59.870 --> 01:38:01.910
There's a lot of confusion out there.

1267
01:38:02.030 --> 01:38:04.110
Is it within the laws of the game?

1268
01:38:04.310 --> 01:38:06.110
Batters can do whatever they want...

1269
01:38:06.230 --> 01:38:09.150
switch from being a righty to a lefty
mid-delivery.


1270
01:38:09.270 --> 01:38:11.390
Switch hit, reverse sweep...
are all legal.


1271
01:38:11.510 --> 01:38:13.230
Why can't a bowler change her action?

1272
01:38:14.590 --> 01:38:17.110
Sorry, switching from
English to Hindi...


1273
01:38:17.310 --> 01:38:19.470
Is that within the laws of the game?

1274
01:38:19.630 --> 01:38:20.670
Law 21...

1275
01:38:21.470 --> 01:38:24.110
ICC Book of Cricket Rules.
Allowed.


1276
01:38:24.550 --> 01:38:27.870
You can change action.
As long as you bowl with the same hand


1277
01:38:28.150 --> 01:38:30.270
and from the same side of the wicket.

1278
01:38:30.630 --> 01:38:33.070
Anina from the Pavilion End...
spinning around.


1279
01:38:33.350 --> 01:38:34.790
An appeal!

1280
01:38:34.950 --> 01:38:37.110
It's a leg bye.
Struck outside the leg stump.


1281
01:38:37.230 --> 01:38:38.630
End of a unique over.

1282
01:38:38.750 --> 01:38:43.030
"Ghoom Ghoom Ghoomer spinning."

1283
01:38:43.990 --> 01:38:45.950
After the dance performance
of the last over...


1284
01:38:46.230 --> 01:38:47.350
back to cricket.

1285
01:38:47.590 --> 01:38:49.190
Anjali in to Searle.

1286
01:38:49.590 --> 01:38:50.870
It's up in the air...

1287
01:38:52.230 --> 01:38:53.310
And she's out!

1288
01:38:55.910 --> 01:38:58.230
Caught Dipti, bowled Anjali...

1289
01:38:58.350 --> 01:38:59.670
and Anina?

1290
01:38:59.950 --> 01:39:01.790
'Bowling has partnerships too.'

1291
01:39:01.910 --> 01:39:03.990
Sometimes a wicket falls

1292
01:39:04.870 --> 01:39:07.710
'due to pressure created
in the previous over.'


1293
01:39:08.150 --> 01:39:09.750
'Last ball from Anjali.'

1294
01:39:11.030 --> 01:39:12.790
'No runs. End of the over.'

1295
01:39:20.710 --> 01:39:23.990
"Ghoom Ghoom Ghoomer spinning."

1296
01:39:25.710 --> 01:39:27.190
That's my song!

1297
01:39:29.790 --> 01:39:32.470
They think, copyright means...
everyone has the right to copy.


1298
01:39:34.070 --> 01:39:35.270
No... I'll explain later.

1299
01:39:35.710 --> 01:39:37.110
Anina spins again...

1300
01:39:41.990 --> 01:39:44.750
Boom boom boom!
One bullet ball after another.


1301
01:39:46.430 --> 01:39:49.470
'After two balls, the surprise
won't stay a surprise.'


1302
01:39:50.030 --> 01:39:51.630
After zuck zuck zuck...

1303
01:39:53.350 --> 01:39:54.910
...zzzuuuuuck.

1304
01:40:01.030 --> 01:40:04.230
That is her first wicket in cricket.

1305
01:40:04.590 --> 01:40:05.790
'This is called deception.'

1306
01:40:05.910 --> 01:40:08.550
'This is not just a thinking bowler
this is an out-thinking bowler.'


1307
01:40:09.550 --> 01:40:11.750
Great, fantastic, mind-blowing, miracle.

1308
01:40:18.430 --> 01:40:20.110
Beautiful. Beautiful deception.

1309
01:40:20.230 --> 01:40:21.470
Ghoomer became a floater.

1310
01:40:21.590 --> 01:40:24.430
A small change in pace...
Archer back to the pavilion.


1311
01:40:24.550 --> 01:40:27.190
Next in, Camila Williams, the captain.

1312
01:40:27.310 --> 01:40:30.190
Archer telling her, I'm sure,
of Anina's change of pace.


1313
01:40:30.390 --> 01:40:32.150
She just got out, what will she advise!

1314
01:40:32.790 --> 01:40:35.550
Sorry, Williams taking guard.

1315
01:40:41.590 --> 01:40:44.070
Anina... looking for her second wicket.

1316
01:40:44.350 --> 01:40:46.590
The English captain, the best batter
in the team...


1317
01:40:47.030 --> 01:40:47.990
Camila Williams.

1318
01:40:48.110 --> 01:40:50.510
Scored three centuries in
one-day cricket this year.


1319
01:40:50.630 --> 01:40:51.830
Come on, Ani!

1320
01:40:55.310 --> 01:40:55.990
Stumped!

1321
01:41:10.310 --> 01:41:13.630
In the umpire's goggles,
the spinning Ghoomer sees


1322
01:41:13.750 --> 01:41:15.310
Williams coming forward.

1323
01:41:15.710 --> 01:41:18.070
Goggle... became Google.

1324
01:41:18.190 --> 01:41:21.310
If you're not watching this,
you're missing something.


1325
01:41:22.030 --> 01:41:25.750
'Get to the ground, get to a TV,
radio, phone...'


1326
01:41:25.870 --> 01:41:27.070
'get to something.'

1327
01:41:27.190 --> 01:41:29.270
'Cricket is being Ghoomered!'

1328
01:41:35.550 --> 01:41:37.310
Bowling change from the far end.

1329
01:41:37.870 --> 01:41:40.350
Bernadette thrashes this one for 4.

1330
01:41:40.870 --> 01:41:41.870
'Cracking shot!'

1331
01:41:43.270 --> 01:41:46.350
'Looks like the English have decided to
go after the bowling at the other end.'


1332
01:41:46.470 --> 01:41:48.550
16 runs from that over.

1333
01:41:53.750 --> 01:41:55.110
Start of Ghoomer's third over.

1334
01:42:01.430 --> 01:42:02.390
Come on.

1335
01:42:02.510 --> 01:42:04.430
An easy catch dropped in the slips.

1336
01:42:04.950 --> 01:42:05.750
Sorry...

1337
01:42:05.870 --> 01:42:07.230
commentator... neutral...

1338
01:42:07.550 --> 01:42:08.470
Stiff upper lip.

1339
01:42:08.590 --> 01:42:09.550
I'm an Aussie.

1340
01:42:09.790 --> 01:42:10.630
Sorry, mate.

1341
01:42:11.030 --> 01:42:12.030
Next ball.

1342
01:42:12.870 --> 01:42:13.550
Shot!

1343
01:42:13.670 --> 01:42:16.630
Over the long on boundary... 6 runs.

1344
01:42:16.830 --> 01:42:19.350
The ball was a bit short,
easily hit for 6.


1345
01:42:19.950 --> 01:42:21.110
Next ball.

1346
01:42:21.590 --> 01:42:24.550
Short and Bernadette pulls it
through square leg for 4.


1347
01:42:24.670 --> 01:42:27.510
The English batters have decided,
attack is the best form of defence.


1348
01:42:27.630 --> 01:42:28.470
What a shot! 4 runs!

1349
01:42:28.750 --> 01:42:31.710
'Has the dropped catch
affected her length, I wonder.'


1350
01:42:32.670 --> 01:42:34.830
Looks like Bernadette
has managed to rattle her


1351
01:42:34.950 --> 01:42:35.710
with her aggression.

1352
01:42:35.830 --> 01:42:37.670
Fantastic batting by Bernadette.

1353
01:42:37.790 --> 01:42:39.470
Pin-drop silence in the stadium.

1354
01:42:42.230 --> 01:42:43.830
Anina in deep thought.

1355
01:42:48.750 --> 01:42:49.230
Yes!

1356
01:42:49.350 --> 01:42:50.550
'Clean bowled!'

1357
01:42:51.190 --> 01:42:54.070
When you bowl a yorker

1358
01:42:54.310 --> 01:42:57.150
the greatest batter looks like a joker.

1359
01:42:57.870 --> 01:42:58.390
Sorry.

1360
01:42:58.510 --> 01:43:01.150
Poetry in cricket brings out
the poet in me.


1361
01:43:01.270 --> 01:43:04.430
116 for 4. And I'm so sorry
to be breaking into Hindi.


1362
01:43:04.670 --> 01:43:05.710
Sounds beautiful.

1363
01:43:12.190 --> 01:43:14.870
Just a one step run-up
but what a fast yorker!


1364
01:43:16.190 --> 01:43:18.390
The concentration-smoothie-effect.

1365
01:43:21.430 --> 01:43:22.590
Ghoomer!

1366
01:43:26.190 --> 01:43:27.590
Spin from the other end too.

1367
01:43:29.470 --> 01:43:31.190
'A good shot... boundary.'

1368
01:43:32.270 --> 01:43:33.590
'Nasreen right-arm over.'

1369
01:43:33.790 --> 01:43:36.470
'Played towards midwicket... 1 run.'

1370
01:43:37.030 --> 01:43:38.150
'Next ball.'

1371
01:43:38.350 --> 01:43:40.790
'Great shot... ball is in the air...'

1372
01:43:40.910 --> 01:43:41.710
Out!

1373
01:43:42.790 --> 01:43:45.110
With that, England lose
their fifth wicket.


1374
01:43:46.470 --> 01:43:48.630
End of a successful over by Nasreen.

1375
01:43:51.230 --> 01:43:52.630
'Anina's fourth over...'

1376
01:43:53.230 --> 01:43:55.990
Looks like the captain will make
her bowl all 10 overs together


1377
01:43:56.190 --> 01:43:58.430
that is if England isn't bowled out
by then!


1378
01:43:59.870 --> 01:44:01.870
A non-Ghoomer delivery.
Lot of spin.


1379
01:44:04.070 --> 01:44:05.990
Straight action... sharp turn again.

1380
01:44:06.550 --> 01:44:07.950
The batter expecting a Ghoomer

1381
01:44:08.070 --> 01:44:10.390
but Anina bowling straight
and deceiving her.


1382
01:44:13.030 --> 01:44:14.230
The ball is in the air...

1383
01:44:15.070 --> 01:44:16.670
MINE!

1384
01:44:23.670 --> 01:44:24.950
She drops it.

1385
01:44:25.190 --> 01:44:27.590
That was a wrong one
that deceived Amber.


1386
01:44:29.630 --> 01:44:32.070
There was no time
for catching practice!


1387
01:44:32.430 --> 01:44:34.310
The ball was on Anina's
right side...


1388
01:44:34.430 --> 01:44:36.710
maybe someone else
should've gone for it.


1389
01:44:36.830 --> 01:44:39.150
Maybe someone else
should've been commentating.


1390
01:44:41.550 --> 01:44:43.790
A Jonty Rhodes like you
also misses a catch!


1391
01:44:44.030 --> 01:44:46.710
Mr Sunny is commentating over there,
may I sit here?


1392
01:44:46.830 --> 01:44:48.310
- But, sir...
- I'm fine.


1393
01:44:48.630 --> 01:44:49.950
Please carry on.

1394
01:44:50.070 --> 01:44:52.630
And to bowl the over's
last delivery, Amit--


1395
01:44:52.750 --> 01:44:54.550
er, Anina comes in.

1396
01:44:57.510 --> 01:44:59.110
And Amber out.
Caught and bowled!


1397
01:44:59.230 --> 01:45:00.150
Great catch.

1398
01:45:03.110 --> 01:45:03.910
Fluke!

1399
01:45:04.790 --> 01:45:07.110
It looks like, she has hurt herself.

1400
01:45:11.550 --> 01:45:12.950
The physio coming on to the field.

1401
01:45:15.390 --> 01:45:17.550
'Anina is leaving the field.'

1402
01:45:19.350 --> 01:45:21.470
Even if she retires hurt now...

1403
01:45:21.830 --> 01:45:25.390
she will have left her mark
in cricketing history.


1404
01:45:25.710 --> 01:45:28.430
Only those who have no desire
to move forward...


1405
01:45:28.910 --> 01:45:30.510
look back at their achievements.

1406
01:45:30.670 --> 01:45:32.870
Don't look back.
The camera is on you.


1407
01:45:34.390 --> 01:45:36.310
4 overs 28 runs and 4 wickets.

1408
01:45:38.150 --> 01:45:39.190
Hello.

1409
01:45:41.430 --> 01:45:42.350
May I go in?

1410
01:45:43.190 --> 01:45:44.190
Are you ice?

1411
01:45:45.630 --> 01:45:47.430
Then you have no work inside.

1412
01:45:54.430 --> 01:45:56.630
Goes on her knees,
clears the boundary,


1413
01:45:56.870 --> 01:45:57.470
6 runs.

1414
01:45:59.470 --> 01:46:01.550
A lofted shot straight to long on.

1415
01:46:02.350 --> 01:46:03.910
Oh ho... 4 runs.

1416
01:46:04.030 --> 01:46:06.150
Played between point and gully...

1417
01:46:08.670 --> 01:46:10.830
Whacked over mid on...

1418
01:46:11.110 --> 01:46:12.150
What are they bowling?

1419
01:46:12.630 --> 01:46:14.670
Drives through extra cover for 4.

1420
01:46:15.550 --> 01:46:17.470
Ball is in the air... 6 runs!

1421
01:46:18.630 --> 01:46:19.790
Welcome back, Amitabh.

1422
01:46:19.910 --> 01:46:22.830
Looks like a whole new game out there
without the left-arm Ghoomer.


1423
01:46:23.230 --> 01:46:25.710
'England's middle order wreaking havoc
in Anina's absence.'


1424
01:46:25.830 --> 01:46:26.510
Go.

1425
01:46:26.630 --> 01:46:27.750
'India again on the back foot.'

1426
01:46:27.870 --> 01:46:28.590
Go!

1427
01:46:34.110 --> 01:46:35.110
According to the rules...

1428
01:46:35.230 --> 01:46:37.230
when a bowler stays off the field
for a period of time...


1429
01:46:37.430 --> 01:46:39.670
she has to wait
for the same amount of time...


1430
01:46:39.790 --> 01:46:40.950
to bowl again.

1431
01:46:41.230 --> 01:46:44.310
Batsman can retire hurt and
come back anytime and play.


1432
01:46:45.190 --> 01:46:46.990
But a bowler has
to come back and wait.

1433
01:46:47.110 --> 01:46:48.070
Who made these rules?

1434
01:46:48.510 --> 01:46:50.550
You know, the Brits owe us
more than one explanation.


1435
01:46:51.710 --> 01:46:52.870
Lofted... 4 runs.

1436
01:46:52.990 --> 01:46:54.070
A great cover drive.

1437
01:46:54.190 --> 01:46:56.030
Shot! No fielder at deep midwicket...

1438
01:46:56.150 --> 01:46:58.110
England know that they have a few overs

1439
01:46:58.230 --> 01:46:59.550
before Anina returns to bowl

1440
01:46:59.670 --> 01:47:01.910
and boy, are they cashing
in before that.


1441
01:47:02.790 --> 01:47:04.470
Played towards midwicket,

1442
01:47:04.590 --> 01:47:07.510
first run taken quickly...
Anina's dive saves a boundary.


1443
01:47:07.790 --> 01:47:09.430
And... a strong throw...

1444
01:47:09.590 --> 01:47:11.230
this can be a close call.

1445
01:47:11.390 --> 01:47:12.670
240 for 7.

1446
01:47:15.750 --> 01:47:16.990
Referred to the third umpire.

1447
01:47:17.150 --> 01:47:18.630
Why do you need a third umpire?

1448
01:47:20.550 --> 01:47:21.670
And that's out!

1449
01:47:25.270 --> 01:47:27.070
A run out is not a bowler's wicket.

1450
01:47:31.390 --> 01:47:33.510
Captain Dipti speaking to the umpire.

1451
01:47:38.390 --> 01:47:40.430
'The entire stadium has come alive.'

1452
01:47:41.910 --> 01:47:43.030
Ghoomer!

1453
01:47:46.470 --> 01:47:48.590
'Anina's fifth over
from the Pavilion End.'


1454
01:47:53.350 --> 01:47:54.590
The field is spread out.

1455
01:47:54.830 --> 01:47:58.270
Let's see if Anina's injury
will affect her bowling.


1456
01:47:59.030 --> 01:48:00.190
Nicole on strike.

1457
01:48:01.310 --> 01:48:03.030
Anina, left arm, around the wicket.

1458
01:48:04.470 --> 01:48:06.470
The shot piercing the field...

1459
01:48:09.150 --> 01:48:10.510
A change in the field.

1460
01:48:10.830 --> 01:48:13.670
Fielders are being brought in
instead of being spread out!


1461
01:48:14.070 --> 01:48:15.110
What's going on?

1462
01:48:16.670 --> 01:48:18.670
Slips, gully, forward short leg
and silly point?


1463
01:48:18.910 --> 01:48:20.150
Ghoomer thinking!

1464
01:48:20.390 --> 01:48:21.670
'Hurt the ego.'

1465
01:48:22.070 --> 01:48:23.270
'You won't need to take the wicket,'

1466
01:48:23.390 --> 01:48:24.790
'the batter will give it away herself.'

1467
01:48:25.310 --> 01:48:27.030
A drunkard bowling to me?

1468
01:48:27.390 --> 01:48:30.870
'This ego led someone to give up
their wicket.'


1469
01:48:31.430 --> 01:48:32.350
Remember?

1470
01:48:35.870 --> 01:48:36.590
Out!

1471
01:48:36.950 --> 01:48:39.390
It's a five-wicket haul on debut

1472
01:48:39.510 --> 01:48:40.670
for this cricketing wonder.

1473
01:48:40.790 --> 01:48:42.870
A bouncer from a spinner!

1474
01:48:43.430 --> 01:48:44.270
Spinner?

1475
01:48:44.670 --> 01:48:45.190
Pfft!

1476
01:49:01.910 --> 01:49:03.670
266 for 8 wickets.

1477
01:49:03.870 --> 01:49:05.950
Dipti, right-arm over the wicket.

1478
01:49:06.430 --> 01:49:07.350
That's leg before.

1479
01:49:07.470 --> 01:49:08.790
And that's the 9th wicket.

1480
01:49:11.870 --> 01:49:12.870
Clean bowled.

1481
01:49:12.990 --> 01:49:16.110
England all out for 266.

1482
01:49:16.470 --> 01:49:18.630
12 overs wasted.

1483
01:49:18.870 --> 01:49:21.630
Wickets falling in a heap at the end.

1484
01:49:30.630 --> 01:49:33.190
And after all that drama,
it's a pretty decent score


1485
01:49:33.310 --> 01:49:35.550
which will require some getting.

1486
01:49:35.670 --> 01:49:37.830
Remember India have just 10 batters.

1487
01:49:37.950 --> 01:49:39.790
The Ghoomer does not bat.

1488
01:49:39.910 --> 01:49:41.070
SKY bowls?

1489
01:49:41.190 --> 01:49:42.030
Virat bowls?

1490
01:49:42.150 --> 01:49:43.910
Rohit bowls? KL bowls?

1491
01:49:44.310 --> 01:49:45.550
Batters don't bowl...

1492
01:49:45.670 --> 01:49:47.070
why should she have to bat?

1493
01:49:51.590 --> 01:49:52.710
Before she can catch her breath...

1494
01:49:52.830 --> 01:49:54.830
they start hounding with mics
and questions.


1495
01:49:55.110 --> 01:49:56.550
Let the match get over first!

1496
01:50:06.510 --> 01:50:07.710
Sir?

1497
01:50:10.630 --> 01:50:13.230
They say, you can't clap
with one hand.


1498
01:50:13.350 --> 01:50:16.350
But this one hand
has created an applause


1499
01:50:16.470 --> 01:50:18.430
that will echo for years.

1500
01:50:28.150 --> 01:50:30.350
- Hello?
- 'What fabulous bowling, Ghoomer!'


1501
01:50:30.470 --> 01:50:31.870
Rasika, why aren't you here?

1502
01:50:31.990 --> 01:50:34.430
Paddy brother said, in the ground
you can't see much from a distance


1503
01:50:34.550 --> 01:50:35.270
TV is better.

1504
01:50:36.950 --> 01:50:40.150
Start of the Indian innings...
target 267.


1505
01:50:41.110 --> 01:50:44.070
Evans to Dipti,
right-arm over the wicket.


1506
01:50:45.310 --> 01:50:46.990
Cracking shot.

1507
01:50:47.350 --> 01:50:49.230
'The Indian innings on its way.'

1508
01:50:50.230 --> 01:50:52.710
Outside off, played between
gully and point... 4 runs.


1509
01:50:56.070 --> 01:50:58.550
Great timing. No chance to stop it.

1510
01:50:59.910 --> 01:51:00.670
Oh ho ho!

1511
01:51:00.790 --> 01:51:03.030
Wherever you place the fielders,
we'll hit it over them.


1512
01:51:03.510 --> 01:51:05.110
Dipti off to a flyer.

1513
01:51:06.230 --> 01:51:07.110
An appeal...

1514
01:51:07.590 --> 01:51:08.310
and out!

1515
01:51:08.790 --> 01:51:10.190
India lose their first wicket.

1516
01:51:14.950 --> 01:51:16.750
Trying to steal a single here...

1517
01:51:17.430 --> 01:51:18.350
saved by a whisker.

1518
01:51:18.470 --> 01:51:19.990
That could've been a run out.

1519
01:51:20.150 --> 01:51:22.190
We have 38 overs.
We need only 5 runs per over.


1520
01:51:24.190 --> 01:51:25.030
Way outside off.

1521
01:51:25.150 --> 01:51:25.990
Play straight.

1522
01:51:28.070 --> 01:51:31.310
For her, playing straight means
straight over mid off.


1523
01:51:32.430 --> 01:51:35.070
Runs flowing off Dipti's bat.

1524
01:51:35.270 --> 01:51:37.390
This crazy girl is batting like
it's a T20.


1525
01:51:37.510 --> 01:51:39.870
- You won't get a chance to bat.
- Shall I take off my pads?


1526
01:51:43.750 --> 01:51:44.710
Next ball.

1527
01:51:44.830 --> 01:51:46.150
A bullet-like straight drive.

1528
01:51:46.270 --> 01:51:47.270
Shot!

1529
01:51:49.790 --> 01:51:51.390
- Are you okay?
- Yes, sir.


1530
01:51:52.030 --> 01:51:53.070
Williams to Shreya.

1531
01:51:53.350 --> 01:51:54.190
Driven square.

1532
01:52:03.110 --> 01:52:04.350
Bernadette to Shreya...

1533
01:52:05.190 --> 01:52:06.310
And... out!

1534
01:52:06.670 --> 01:52:07.670
Caught and bowled.

1535
01:52:11.030 --> 01:52:11.870
Next ball...

1536
01:52:13.310 --> 01:52:14.150
played in the air...

1537
01:52:14.270 --> 01:52:15.870
a fielder coming under it... and out!

1538
01:52:15.990 --> 01:52:17.390
Third wicket down for India.

1539
01:52:17.670 --> 01:52:19.190
Beautifully done there by England.

1540
01:52:21.110 --> 01:52:21.950
A flighted delivery...

1541
01:52:22.390 --> 01:52:23.270
bowled!

1542
01:52:24.870 --> 01:52:27.870
Within a few moments,
a cloud of gloom has descended.


1543
01:52:33.110 --> 01:52:34.350
A cracking shot by Dipti.

1544
01:52:34.870 --> 01:52:35.710
Out!

1545
01:52:37.590 --> 01:52:40.030
'Right shot but the placement
was wrong.'


1546
01:52:42.150 --> 01:52:45.110
This is called snatching defeat
from the jaws of victory!


1547
01:52:47.590 --> 01:52:49.150
We can still win it.
Play out Evans--


1548
01:52:49.790 --> 01:52:53.270
Cricket can be a funny game but
the Indians are not laughing.


1549
01:52:53.470 --> 01:52:55.750
Williams with four wickets
and her tail up...


1550
01:52:55.870 --> 01:52:58.190
just two wickets to go
for an English win.


1551
01:52:58.510 --> 01:53:00.630
31 runs for an Indian win.

1552
01:53:01.470 --> 01:53:02.350
Williams' next ball...

1553
01:53:04.110 --> 01:53:05.870
Sets off for a quick single.

1554
01:53:06.150 --> 01:53:07.550
This could be close.

1555
01:53:10.750 --> 01:53:11.710
Super shot!

1556
01:53:11.910 --> 01:53:13.350
Played in the gap...

1557
01:53:13.790 --> 01:53:15.950
fielder dives... 4 runs.

1558
01:53:17.070 --> 01:53:18.430
Another great shot.

1559
01:53:19.110 --> 01:53:20.830
Defensive push.
Another misfield.


1560
01:53:21.430 --> 01:53:22.310
Bernadette.

1561
01:53:22.870 --> 01:53:23.910
Yorker.

1562
01:53:24.710 --> 01:53:26.150
Tempers going up in the field.

1563
01:53:26.350 --> 01:53:28.670
It's all about who keeps a cooler head.

1564
01:53:29.950 --> 01:53:31.470
A gentle push for 1 run.

1565
01:53:32.510 --> 01:53:35.350
Runs coming in singles,
India moving towards its target.


1566
01:53:40.710 --> 01:53:41.590
Another single.

1567
01:53:41.710 --> 01:53:43.550
Just simple responsible batting

1568
01:53:43.670 --> 01:53:45.870
has put India back in the driver's seat.

1569
01:53:45.990 --> 01:53:47.510
Only 10 more runs to win.

1570
01:53:47.630 --> 01:53:50.270
Fantastic shot... 6 runs.

1571
01:53:50.510 --> 01:53:51.830
Only 4 more runs to win.

1572
01:53:52.350 --> 01:53:54.030
It's good to see you smiling again.

1573
01:53:54.190 --> 01:53:56.030
We Indians have a great
